"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-rapper-snoop-dogg-to-carry-paris-olympics-2024-torch-breaking-celeb-news\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbRapper Snoop Dogg to carry Paris Olympics 2024 torch  American rapper Snoop Dogg will carry the Olympic flame through Saint-Denis on Friday ahead of the Paris Olympics 2024 opening ceremony.  American rapperSnoop Doggwillcarry the Olympic flamethrough Saint-Denis on Friday, marking a significant moment before theParis Olympics 2024opening ceremony.  Joining him will be French actressLaetitia Casta, French rapperMC Solaar, and retired Ukrainian pole-vaulterSergey Bubka.  Snoop Dogg will carry it through the streets of Saint-Denis, the ethnically diverse northern Paris suburb that is home to the Olympic Stadium and Aquatics Centre, the town's mayor Mathieu Hanotin told AFP on Monday.  The Olympic flame has spent two months crossing France, and Friday morning it will be carried through the athletes' village which straddles Saint-Denis\\u00a0and neighbouring Saint-Ouen, before going to the Olympic Stadium and the Aquatics Centre a few kilometres away.  Snoop Dogg, 52, was born in greater Los Angeles, which will host the next Games in 2028.  The torch relay will not be the rapper's only appearance at the Paris Olympics 2024\\u00a0as he will also be an Olympic commentator for US television station NBC.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"